tl;dr need to fix synchronizer

There is a network made of four nodes. The first peer receives an infinite stream of transactions. All the received transactions are being committed. After some time, the third peer goes offline. The degraded network continues to commit arriving transactions. After some time again, the third peer wakes up. The network is still under of incoming transactions.

Actual result: no more new blocks appear in the blockstore of the third peer. No synchronization process is going.

Expected result: the third peer should start synchronisation with the network state.

 

Reproducible on commit {{c04712dd6aeb38dfef}}

To reproduce on a single host machine you have to start four postgreses in docker. Use attached files.

Attachments also contain a python script for infinite transactions generation with patched irohalib files (because it was broken on the commit). Script launch format is:
