Find a way to get if a user has already been granted a permission. Currently if you grant a permission that is already present, then the transaction fails (and if it is part of an atomic batch of transactions, the entire batch fails).

The issue is that now Iroha does not allow to list the permissions were granted to an account (except the indirect way mentioned above).
Looks like the problem can be solved by extension of AccountResponse message schema:

{code}
message AccountResponse {
    Account account = 1;
    repeated string account_roles = 2;
}
{code}

 ... needs to be accomplished with the granted permissions field:
{code}
// an existing message from commands.proto
message GrantPermission {
    string account_id = 1;
    GrantablePermission permission = 2;
}

message AccountResponse {
    Account account = 1;
    repeated string account_roles = 2;
    repeated GrantPermission granted_permissions = 3;
    // where granted_permissions[n].account_id is the id of a person who has granted 
    //granted_permissions[n].permission the AccountResponse.account.account_id
}
{code}

